cs.IT, cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with wireless communication and power transfer, which falls under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT). The use of game theory to develop a distributed power splitting framework suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Game Theory and Economics (cs.GT). The paper also involves the use of relays, which could place it under the sub-category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The analysis of Nash equilibriums and the development of a distributed algorithm suggest that it could also belong to the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the use of simulations to validate the theoretical analyses suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Multimedia (cs.MM).
